# Windows Build Workflow

- On Windows, always use:

```bat
./compilar_dev.bat
```

- `compilar_dev.bat` already:
  - compiles the project
  - launches the compiled executable automatically (`build/SeqChecker.exe`)

- Never run the executable manually after running `./compilar_dev.bat`, unless explicitly requested.

- Never perform clean builds automatically.

- Never delete, wipe, or recreate the build folder unless explicitly requested.

- Always preserve the previous compilation and incremental build cache.

- If compilation fails, try to fix the issue without cleaning the build directory first.

- After a relevant (non-trivial) change, always bump the app version by `+0.001` using `docs/ChangeLog.md` as the human source of truth:
  - Add a new top changelog entry with the new version number.
  - The changelog must always be written in castellano (Spanish).
  - At the end of the new changelog note, add a short suggested commit name inside `[]`. Este nombre debe estar en castellano. Ejemplo [SeqChecker - Listado copiable de frames corruptos]
- After updating `docs/ChangeLog.md`, run:

```bat
./sync_version.bat
```

- `sync_version.bat` (via `tools/sync_version.py`) synchronizes the version surfaces `VERSION` and `CMakeLists.txt` against `docs/ChangeLog.md`, resolving to `max(CMake, ChangeLog)`. The app runtime version must come from CMake's `PROJECT_VERSION` (exposed as the `SEQCHECKER_VERSION` compile definition).
- Do not manually edit version numbers in `src/main.cpp`, `VERSION`, or `CMakeLists.txt` unless the version sync script itself is being updated.
- Do not recompile again after bumping/synchronizing the app version.

## Language Policy

- **UI text (user-visible)**: always in English.
  - Labels, buttons, checkboxes, tooltips, status texts, placeholders, dialog titles/messages, table headers, empty-state messages.
- **Code comments and debug logs**: always in Spanish (developer language).
  - `CONDITIONAL_DEBUG(...)`, `qDebug()`, `qWarning()`, inline `//` comments, block `/* */` comments.
- **Internal error strings** (logged, not rendered in UI): Spanish is fine.
- When adding new UI text, write it in English. When adding comments or debug output, write in Spanish.
- **Changelog policy**: `docs/ChangeLog.md` must always be written in castellano (Spanish).

## UI Style Policy

- Follow the shared LGA UI style guide: `C:\Portable\LGA_MediaTools_v2\docs\UI_STYLE_LGA_APPS.md`.
- Centralize colors/metrics as tokens in `include/seqchecker/mainwindow.h` (e.g. `COL_*`, `DROP_OVERLAY_*`); do not hardcode colors inline in feature code.
- Base font is `Inter`; dark theme tokens come from `resources/styles/dark_theme.qss` + `tabs.qss`.

## Tooltip Policy

- This app currently uses native Qt tooltips (`widget->setToolTip(...)` / `QTableWidgetItem::setToolTip(...)`); it does NOT yet port `CustomTooltip` from MediaTools/PipeSync.
- Keep tooltip text short and in English.
- If a richer tooltip system is needed later, port `CustomTooltip` from MediaTools and migrate native tooltips, mirroring the PipeSync shortcut format. Until then, native tooltips are acceptable.

## Python Backend Policy

- The detector lives in `py_scr/LGA_SeqChecker.py`. It must keep emitting one JSON line per event on stdout with the `MT_` protocol consumed by `MainWindow::onPythonLine()`:
  - `MT_SEQ_FOUND`, `MT_PROGRESS`, `MT_SEQ_RESULT`, `MT_DONE`.
- Binaries are resolved relative to the script (`thirdparty/win/OpenEXR/exrcheck.exe`, `exrheader.exe`); do not hardcode absolute paths.
- `compilar_dev.bat` copies `py_scr` into `build/py_scr` on every build; in dev mode `python_runtime`, `thirdparty` and `config` are resolved from the project root, so they are not copied into `build`.
